  "prompt": "Is mercury a radioactive element?",
  "response": "Mercury (Hg) is not generally considered a radioactive element. It is a heavy metal and exists in many stable isotopic forms, with mercury-202 being the most common. However, mercury does have some isotopes that are radioactive, such as mercury-194 and mercury-203, but these are not naturally abundant. Most of the mercury found in natural and industrial environments is stable and non-radioactive.",
